{
  "texts": [
    "The post-alignment loss component L post as mean squared error between Q s ∘ F and Q t masked over T s+t,",
    "The pre-alignment similarity loss incentives generation of non-trivial encodings by maximizing the encoding difference before the alignment transformation.",
    "In order to increase feature density, we introduce best sample similarity error.",
    "We first divide the encodings into a set of nonoverlapping chunks, U.",
    "In our experiments, we used square chunks with width and height of 32 pixels."
  ]
}